    "notes": "Detection should key on whoami /all, net user /domain, or query user spawned by a parent process residing in AppData\\Roaming. The combination of (1) user-discovery commands AND (2) a non-standard AppData parent is the high-fidelity signal. Benign events use the same commands but are parented by cmd.exe or explorer.exe — do NOT alert on parent path = System32 or Windows. Consider a sequence/correlation rule: 2+ discovery commands from the same parent PID within 30 seconds is near-certain C2 enumeration."
